Master Answer:
Groups who are eligible to receive the influenza vaccine (flu shot) for free include people who provide essential community services such as police officers, firefighters and ambulance attendants. For information on whether an annual flu shot is required by your employer while on duty, please contact your occupational health or human resources department. Find a flu clinic near you here.
